```java
@Override
public boolean onOptionsItemSelected(MenuItem item) {
    switch (item.getItemId()) {
        case R.id.rssi:
            View menuItemView = findViewById(R.id.rssi);

            // create PopupWindow with custom layout.
           LayoutInflater inflater = (LayoutInflater) getSystemService(LAYOUT_INFLATER_SERVICE);
           View popupView = inflater.inflate(R.layout.my_popup_layout, null);

           int width = LinearLayout.LayoutParams.WRAP_CONTENT;
           int height = LinearLayout.LayoutParams.WRAP_CONTENT;

           final PopupWindow popupWindow = new PopupWindow(popupView, width, height);

          TextView textPopupIntValue=popupView.findViewById(R.id.textViewIntValue);
          textPopupIntValue.setText("Your Integer Here!");

          // Show the popup window on app
         popupWindow.showAsDropDown(menuItemView);

         return true;

       default:
         return super.onOptionsItemSelected(item);
      }
}
```

This will stimulate syntax appeal by creating a personalized snazzy bubble whenever your menu item is engaged. Remember to replace "my_popup_layout" and "textViewIntValue" with your actual layout ID and TextView ID respectively.

